## schemaValidator

Unlike the rest of the casinocoin-libjs API, schemaValidator is a static object on CasinocoinAPI. It provides utility methods that do not use a server.

## schemaValidate

`CasinocoinAPI.schemaValidator.schemaValidate(schemaName: string, object: any): void`

This method checks an object for conformance to a specified schema. It does not return anything, but will throw a `ValidationError` if the object does not conform to the schema.

### Example

```javascript
CasinocoinAPI.schemaValidator.schemaValidate('sign', {
    signedTransaction: '',
    id: '65469B8745DA8AD3B53E6DE410081553E451EEBB03D10DA054C5E7A980CE28FB'
})
```

```json
undefined
```

If the object is valid (conforms to the schema), nothing is returned. Otherwise, `schemaValidate` throws an error:

```javascript
CasinocoinAPI.schemaValidator.schemaValidate('sign', {
    signedTransaction: '',
    id: '123'
})
```

```
[ValidationError(instance.id does not match pattern "^[A-F0-9]{64}$")]
```
